# .opsec.local — machine-specific values to scan for in commits.
# Copy to .opsec.local and fill in your values. Gitignored.
#
# One entry per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# Format: VALUE or SEVERITY:VALUE
#   fail:  blocks commit (default if no prefix)
#   warn:  prints warning but doesn't block
#
# The scanner also reads .env values automatically — no need to
# duplicate those here.

# Your usernames / identity (warn — may appear in comments legitimately)
# warn:my-username

# Your email (the scanner already catches generic emails as warn; add
# your own as fail if you want a hard block)
# fail:me@example.com

# Machine-local paths that shouldn't appear in tracked files
# /home/me/my-private-project

# parse-cc-specific: anything you've fed into TaskCreate/TaskUpdate
# metadata fields that shouldn't end up in the audit corpus on commit.
# These are *property names* — the corpus stores them when the audit's
# allowlist doesn't already collapse the metadata position. Most users
# won't need to add anything here; entries belong here only when the
# allowlist isn't sufficient for your workflow.
# fail:my-private-task-tag
